	  <h2>Homework no. 2</h2>
	  <p> The homework no. 2 is strictly optional and has no
	    influence on your final marks.  Working on it lets you
	    test your understanding of the subject and prepare for the
	    written test.</p>

	  <p>The <a href="hw02.pdf">text of the problems</a> is
	    now available for download.</p>

	  <p>The data required for problem 3 can be downloaded from
	  the <a href="http:math.nist.gov">Math, Statistics, and
	  Computational Science site</a> of
	  the <a href="www.nist.gov">U.S National Institute of
	  Standards and Technology</a>:<ul>
	    <li>the <a href="ftp://math.nist.gov/pub/MatrixMarket2/Harwell-Boeing/bcsstruc1/bcsstk05.mtx.gz">stiffness matrix</a>,
	    </li>
	    <li>the <a href="ftp://math.nist.gov/pub/MatrixMarket2/Harwell-Boeing/bcsstruc1/bcsstm05.mtx.gz">mass matrix</a>.
	    </li>
	  </ul></p>

	  <p> A brief description of the format used to describe the
	    matrices <a href="http://math.nist.gov/MatrixMarket/formats.html#mtx">is
	      available on the same site</a>.</p>
